Trias Natura — Canonical Principle

A system that seeks truth in nature must rest on three independent legs: memory, measurement, and verification. Remove one, and certainty collapses.

It sits coherently alongside the other triadic structures:

Doctrine
Three Legs
Trias Natura: memory • measurement • verification

Tritestium: human witness • observational witness • laboratory witness

Ecological Gate Logic: PoRH • PoP • PoR

Together they form a consistent architecture:
	•	Memory preserves long-duration observation (culture, stories, precedent).
	•	Measurement observes the present state (sensors, science, field observation).
	•	Verification tests endurance through time (Boolean gates, ecological outcomes).

